/* 
Local variables - variables which are declared or initialized inside
the functions and its scope is limited within the function.Default value of local variable
is garbage value.

Global variables - variables which are declared or initialized outside
the functions and can be used anywere in the program are called global variables.
Default value of global variable is 0.


Actual parameters - parameters or expression which are called inside
the main function are called actual parameters.


Formal parameters - formal parameters are local variables which are assinged values 
from the arguments when the function is called.

arguments - variables which are passed from the main function to a formal parameter is known as arguments.
*/